  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Risks by Score is used to understand the potential impact of risk to the project.&amp;nbsp; Addressing risks according to&#xD;
    their likelihood of occurrence and potential impact is essential for project health.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To calculate Risk Score:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Assign the following values to each&amp;nbsp;project risk: &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Likelihood of occurrence - defined as a percentage. Use a standard scale such as 20% (low likelihood of&#xD;
                occurrence), 40%, 60%, 80% (high likelihood of occurrence)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Estimated Cost of Impact - defined in hours or day&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Calculate a risk exposure score for each risk&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Risk Score = Likelihood of occurrence * Estimated Cost of Impact&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Establish ranges of scores to group results.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A good way to monitor Risk by Score is to use a bar chart. Plot the number of risks on the Y axis and risk score ranges&#xD;
    on the X axis. Watch out for a high number of risks in the highest risk score ranges.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>Identify&amp;nbsp;those risks&amp;nbsp;with the highest risk scores and determine what activities are required to mitigate them&#xD;
(e.g. get clarification from stakeholders, resolve issues with new technologies).&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Below is an example of a Risk by Score chart for the Online Auction project in Smarter Planet program. Notice that the&#xD;
    majority of risks are in the lowest risk score range. Only one risk is in the highest impact range. X-axis in the chart&#xD;
    represents the score rank in percentages and the Y-axis is the number of risks.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;Risks by Score&quot; src=&quot;resources/risk_by_score.gif&quot; width=&quot;471&quot; height=&quot;526&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Frequency and reporting&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Generate a Risks by&amp;nbsp;Score report prior to iteration planning.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Project Conductor&amp;reg; and IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Team Concert&amp;reg; collect risk data. IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Insight&amp;reg; provides&#xD;
    an out of the box report for this metric.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
